  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
ADDRESS INFO for Tina M Flores
Current: 93 Garfield St, Clintonville, WI 54929 United States  (Effective: 12-02-2016)
Prior: 102 Prospect St, Bear Creek, WI 54922
Imposed & stayed sentence - (informational) with Request for Civil judgment

9:16 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Earl Luaders.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  2015CM111 - Atty Luaders confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Atty Luaders enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court recites plea agreement, defendant will plea to count 3 on 2015CM74 and count 1 on 2015CM111.  State concurs.  Atty Luaders concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 3 on 2015CM74 & count 1 as charged on 2015CM111.  Court orders counts 1 & 2 be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Luaders.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2015CM74 (Resisting)

30 days county jail, with huber and to commence within 60 days.  Court will allow the defendant to serve the sentence in another county.
Court costs - Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

2015CM111 (Criminal Damage to property)

45 days county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for a period of 1 year. Consecuctive to any other sentence.  Huber and out of county service if revoked.  1 day of sentence credit.

CONDITIONS:

Court costs
Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.

Court orders the cash bond in 2015CM74 be applied to the court costs.

DNA Sample in both cases.

2015CM111 - Processing

Court adjourned at 9:29 a.m.

Court adjourned at 9:28 a.m.
to the defendant.  Respond on or before June 29, 2015 or warrant will be issued.
